$interpreted: Cell Guard: Who's there!?
Tingko: Sorry to bother you, but Sir Tim would like to talk to the prisoners.
Tingko: Here, for your troubles. Please, enjoy.
Cell Guard: ...How'd you two get in here?
Tingko: Don't worry, we've gotten permission.
Cell Guard: Hmph, looks like those freaks are pretty popular. Getting a lot of visitors...
Cell Guard: Just don't try anything funny...
Tindoiimu: Sophie...
Sophie: Tim!
Tindoiimu: Is everyone okay? Are you hurt?
Sophie: Just some light scratches... but... just...
Sophie: Those people said they're going to confiscate all the money we made, and our props. But we... we did get a permit! It isn't fake!
Ru-yi: Those guards are all so mean! Waahhh~
Hutchinson: Don't cry, Ru-yi! You'll flood the cell...
Hanbei: Hmph... guess the alliance never changes.
Hanbei: Bunch of liars and cheats... And then those greedy jackals that just came by!
Tindoiimu: Someone just came to see you?
Sophie: Yeah, one of those jackal brothers from before. I guess that one was the... younger one?
Sophie: He said he'll smooth everything out for us as long as we give him some money...
Ru-yi: But we don't have that much money~~~!
Hutchinson: Yeah, not unless we sell the whole tent!
Tindoiimu: Those jackals...
Tindoiimu: Sophie, I brought your permit back. Give it a good look.
Sophie: Let me see...
Sophie: ...This permit seems a little different from before...
Hutchinson: You're right!
Hutchinson: The qilin emblem on top was so crisp and clear, but this one seems quite blurry...
Tindoiimu: So this permit really is fake.
Hanbei: But it has the qilin seal on it! How could anyone tell it was fake?
Sophie: How could this happen?
Tindoiimu: Don't worry, I know where the real one is. Just sit tight and let me handle it.
Sophie: Tim... thank you for believing in us, and for all of your help.
Tindoiimu: Of course I believe you! I knew you wouldn't have made a fake permit!
Tingko: Sir, the guards are coming back!
Tindoiimu: Wait here.
Tingko: Sir, it's him!
Younger Jackal: Hoho money money money~
Younger Jackal: With this money I'll be able to leave that stupid theater troupe forever, and my brother can stop breathing down my neck!
Tindoiimu: Hey, they earned that money fair and square! It's not yours to take!
Younger Jackal: I'm sorry, I was... I was under direct orders from the boss!!
Tindoiimu: So your 'boss' told you to blackmail Sophie, too?
Younger Jackal: Uh, that... I... uh...
Tindoiimu: Let's bring him to the authorities, along with the real permit!
Tingko: Yes, sir!
Younger Jackal: That won't matter! Our troupe is in tight with the police!
Tindoiimu: (That must be why their fake permit has an official seal, too... They're working together!)
Younger Jackal: You stay away from me!
Younger Jackal: Boss~!! Boss~!! Help me! I thought we had a dealâ€”!!
Qilin Officer: Shut up, you mangy mutt! I've never seen you before in my life!
Tindoiimu: I found the circus' real permit on him. It has Sophie's name and your official seal.
Tindoiimu: Please let Sophie and them out of their cell.
Qilin Officer: Hmph! How do I know you didn't just make this permit yourself!
Tindoiimu: What, you can't tell one of your own official permits from a counterfeit?
Qilin Officer: I'll be the judge of what's real and what's fake, and the one that girl gave me yesterday was a fake!
Qilin Officer: In the name of justice, I cannot and will not let them out!
Tindoiimu: You...!
Qilin Officer: Now get out of here, I'm busy! If you bother me again, I'll lock you up with her!
Tingko: What should we do next, sir?
Tindoiimu: ...I'm going to break them out of there, even if I have to use force!
